"""
TASK TWO

The program should calculate an entry fee for each player. This calculation should take 
into account the skill level of the player.
The system should display the fee in the appropriate currency, using these exchange rates:
• £ sterling for all UK players; no exchange rate required
• £1 = 1.50 US dollars
• £1 = 2.00 AU dollars.
The entry fee will consist of:
• £10 per player
• an additional fee of £35 for ‘Expert’ players or £20 for ‘Casual’ players.
Fee calculator requirements
• The fee calculator should start with a welcome message. 
• It should ask the user for the player’s:
• email address
• skill level (E for expert, C for casual)
• country (UK, US, AU). 
• It should then calculate the entry fee.
• The fee should be displayed in the correct currency, using the following 
abbreviations: USD, AUD, GBP.
• It should then ask if the user wishes to calculate another fee
"""

#Create initial variables & lists
entryFees = [10,20,35]
useComplete = False
supportedCountries = ['UK','US','AU']

print("Welcome to the fee calculator. Please fill in the fields below:\n================================================================\n")

#Start Program
while useComplete == False:

    #Obtain details from user
    email = input("\nPlease enter your email address: ")

    #Ask for skill level and check if valid
    sValid = False
    while sValid == False:
        skill = input("Please enter your skill level (C=Casual, E=Expert): ")

        if skill == "C":
            skill = "Casual"
            sValid = True
        elif skill == "E":
            skill = "Expert"
            sValid = True
        else:
            print("Invalid, please re-enter")

    #Ask for country and check if valid
    country = input("Please enter your country (UK/US/AU): ")
    
    if not country in supportedCountries:
        print("Sorry this calculator does not support your country's currency")
        break

    #Calculate fee
    fee = entryFees[0]

    #Add skill level fee
    if skill == "C":
        fee += entryFees[1]
    elif skill == "E":
        fee += entryFees[2]

    #Convert to correct currency and display to user
    if country == "US":
        fee *= 1.5
        print("Your entry fee is: {}USD" .format(fee))
    elif country == "AU":
        fee *= 2
        print("Your entry fee is: {}AUD" .format(fee))
    else:
        print("Your entry fee is: {}GBP" .format(fee))

    #Ask user if they want to calculate another fee
    again = input("Would you like to use the fee calculator again (Y/N): ")

    if again == "N":
        break
